---

## Step 1 — Understand the project (15 min, one-time)

Read [CLAUDE.md](CLAUDE.md). Then read the open ADRs in [docs/adr/README.md](docs/adr/README.md).

Goal: know what this project is building and what decisions have already been made.

---

## Step 2 — Pick up a task

Find the lowest-numbered ADR with status **Proposed**. That is the next thing to build.

If all ADRs are Accepted, ask the lead developer what's next.

---

## Step 3 — Set up your environment

1. Clone the repo.
2. Install [Claude Code CLI](https://claude.ai/code) if not already installed.
3. Run `claude` from the repo root and confirm it loads `CLAUDE.md`.
4. Run `make validate-hooks` — all checks should pass green.

_Update this section when the project gains new required tools._

---

## Step 4 — Open your first PR

- Title: one line naming what you built
- Body: one paragraph — what changed and why
- Smoke checklist from `make validate-hooks` checked off

_Update this section with the team's specific PR process._
